metadata.name: Karaja
metadata.description:
Karaja is a etnical group of brazillian indigenous that lives in the Amazon rainforest. They are a simbol of strength and ascertainment. They resist by the time without let your roots die. One of the most treasures of the culture of this people is the tradition of “Hetohoky” party, where they celebrate the passage from childhood to adult life of all children of the comunity. 

NFT: 4724 x 5906 pixels
Phisical Canvas: Oil on Canvas 40x50cm

The buyer can collect a physical Fine Art Print, if interested. (Shipping company and delivery expenses will be provide and paid by the buyer).
